CLOSE An E. coli outbreak has led to the CDC to warn Americans to avoid romaine lettuce and JBS USA to recall close to 100,000 pounds of ground beef.
USA TODAYPresident Donald Trump gives a thumbs-up as he has Thanksgiving Day dinner at his Mar-a-Lago estate in Palm Beach, Florida.
(Photo: Susan Walsh, AP)President Donald Trump was saved from the looming dangers of romaine lettuce on Thanksgiving Day.
Even though the president's Thanksgiving menu with family included a full salad bar with Caesar, wedge and Greek salads, the White House told USA TODAY that no romaine lettuce was served.
Caesar salad is typically made with romaine lettuce.